explanations.reason: The paper focuses on the use of ultrasound technology for detecting and monitoring coronary artery disease (CAD) in a clinical setting. It discusses the development of a programmable ultrasound platform and its application in measuring local vibrations and mechanical strain in cardiac and carotid artery walls. There is no mention of any machine learning techniques, algorithms, or models in the title or abstract, nor any indication that such methods are used in the research described.
